  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study is to evaluate the possible preoperative predictive value of altered
      heart rate variability (HRV) and baroreflex sensitivity in different sleep stages for
      postoperative adverse cardiac events (i.e. arrhythmia or myocardial ischemia needing
      hospitalization or medication, myocardial ischemia assessed by enzyme release, myocardial
      infarction, sudden cardiac death, stroke) in arteriosclerosis obliterans patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
